Death row,
how could you not be?

223
00:08:11,325 --> 00:08:12,994
It was not just that.
When I got there,

224
00:08:13,077 --> 00:08:14,745
it hit me that if I do this,

225
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:16,998
I have a man's life
in my hands.

226
00:08:17,081 --> 00:08:18,374
Rachel, you can handle it.

227
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:19,584
I know I can.

228
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:22,378
Then why do I get
the feeling that something
is bothering you?

229
00:08:22,461 --> 00:08:24,130
Because when
I got back from there,

230
00:08:24,213 --> 00:08:26,048
I was so angry about what
happened to that poor man

231
00:08:26,132 --> 00:08:27,592
that I sat down,
I started working

232
00:08:27,675 --> 00:08:28,759
on this case, and I...

233
00:08:29,135 --> 00:08:30,803
