00:08:50,156 --> 00:08:51,157
And forgetting
about him is healthy?

244
00:08:51,282 --> 00:08:52,491
Isn't that why
you took this case?

245
00:08:52,617 --> 00:08:54,118
To give yourself
something to focus on?

246
00:08:54,619 --> 00:08:56,537
Yes, but I just...
Then don't fight it.

247
00:08:56,954 --> 00:08:58,748
If working to free
an innocent man helps you

248
00:08:58,831 --> 00:09:00,499
to forget about Mike
for a while, he would be

249
00:09:00,583 --> 00:09:02,376
the first person
to tell you to do it.

250
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:07,340
And trust me, if you really
lose yourself in this,

251
00:09:08,341 --> 00:09:10,301
I have a feeling it's going
to seem like a lot less than

252
00:09:10,384 --> 00:09:11,761
two years before he gets out.

253
00:09:23,022 --> 00:09:24,065
LOUIS: Where's Harvey?

254
00:09:24,148 --> 00:09:25,149
Harvey's not here.

255
00:09:25,233 --> 00:09:26,359
Well, get his ass in here,

256
00:09:26,442 --> 00:09:28,194
because he made some goddamn
side deal with those traders

257
00:09:28,277 --> 00:09:29,278
and I want them out.

258
00:09:29,362 --> 00:09:31,864
Louis, I am telling you,
now is not the time.

259
00:09:31,989 --> 00:09:33,991
And I am telling you
that I cannot look

260
00:09:34,075 --> 00:09:36,244
at their smug, stupid faces
for one more day.

261
00:09:36,494 --> 00:09:37,828
Maybe you don't have
to look at them.

262
00:09:38,246 --> 00:09:39,956
What are you talking about?
Louis, did I ever tell you

263
00:09:40,039 --> 00:09:41,582
about my first apartment
in the city?

264
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,084
No.
I was sharing

265
00:09:43,167 --> 00:09:44,585
a 400-square-foot studio

266
00:09:44,669 --> 00:09:47,088
and it was a disaster
until we finally decided

267
00:09:47,171 --> 00:09:49,048
that we had to separate
our spaces for privacy.

268
00:09:49,173 --> 00:09:50,716
Well, this isn't
<i>The Brady Bunch,</i> Donna.

269
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,802
We can't put
a masking tape line down
the center of the office.

270
00:09:52,885 --> 00:09:54,929
I'm not talking
about masking tape, Louis.

271
00:09:55,012 --> 00:09:56,847
I am talking
about hiring an architect

272
00:09:56,931 --> 00:09:58,683
to reconfigure the offices.

273
00:10:00,226 --> 00:10:01,227
(CHUCKLES) You're right.

274
00:10:01,602 --> 00:10:02,895
We can even do
a remodel, which is what

275
00:10:02,979 --> 00:10:04,605
I've been wanting
to do for the last
five years.

276
00:10:04,689 --> 00:10:06,190
And the best part is,
you don't have to deal

277
00:10:06,274 --> 00:10:08,150
with those asshole
traders ever again.

278
00:10:08,234 --> 00:10:09,527
Donna, you're a genius.
I know.

279
00:10:09,694 --> 00:10:11,320
Get me the names of six
architects before lunch.

280
00:10:11,404 --> 00:10:12,780
Louis, you have
your own secretary.

281
00:10:12,863 --> 00:10:14,031
Thanks for nothing.

282
00:10:14,782 --> 00:10:16,325
Why do I even?

283
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:22,748
Nice of you to show up.

284
00:10:22,832 --> 00:10:24,667
I've been peeling
these potatoes by myself.

285
00:10:25,251 --> 00:10:27,420
Sorry, I, uh, got caught up.

286
00:10:27,545 --> 00:10:29,630
Speaking of which,
how did it go
with your lawyer?

287
00:10:30,047 --> 00:10:31,173
You getting out of here?

288
00:10:31,882 --> 00:10:32,925
What?

289
00:10:33,551 --> 00:10:34,510
I'm just kidding.

290
00:10:34,593 --> 00:10:35,594
What's going on?

291
00:10:36,178 --> 00:10:37,179
Nothing.

292
00:10:38,472 --> 00:10:39,473
It's not important.

293
00:10:39,557 --> 00:10:40,975
Your lawyer shows up
