00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:57,366
I'm just not having
a good day.

303
00:10:58,409 --> 00:10:59,493
Hey, it's okay.
Don't sweat it.

304
00:10:59,577 --> 00:11:00,703
All right?

305
00:11:00,786 --> 00:11:02,496
I mean, it's none
of my business anyway.

306
00:11:04,749 --> 00:11:06,292
No, actually,
it is your business.

307
00:11:08,294 --> 00:11:11,630
He came here to tell me
that he tried to get Gallo
transferred, but...

308
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:14,759
It's not going to happen.

309
00:11:15,593 --> 00:11:16,844
Well, as long as
we stick together,

310
00:11:16,927 --> 00:11:18,596
we can deal
with Gallo anyway, right?

311
00:11:20,056 --> 00:11:21,140
Yeah, that's...

312
00:11:21,223 --> 00:11:22,350
That's what I told Harvey.

313
00:11:24,852 --> 00:11:26,187
Well, next time
you talk to him,

314
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:27,438
tell him
I said thanks for trying.

315
00:11:34,070 --> 00:11:35,196
How did it go?
He said he had

316
00:11:35,279 --> 00:11:36,280
to think about it.

317
00:11:36,364 --> 00:11:37,865
What? Why?

318
00:11:37,948 --> 00:11:39,867
Because he's an idiot,
that's why.

319
00:11:40,034 --> 00:11:41,118
So, what are you
going to do?

320
00:11:41,202 --> 00:11:43,162
I'm going to figure out how
to buy us some time.

321
00:11:43,245 --> 00:11:45,122
Well, you better do it fast,
because Cahill's

322
00:11:45,206 --> 00:11:46,916
in your office,
and he wants an answer.

323
00:11:49,835 --> 00:11:50,961
Sean.

324
00:11:51,128 --> 00:11:52,129
What did he say?

325
00:11:52,296 --> 00:11:54,340
He said he wants
to see the details in writing.

326
00:11:54,423 --> 00:11:55,466
I'm not in the mood, Harvey.

327
00:11:55,549 --> 00:11:56,759
And I'm not messing around.

328
00:11:56,842 --> 00:11:58,052
Please tell me
you're kidding me.

329
00:11:58,803 --> 00:12:00,888
Oh, come on,
this is bullshit.
You know my word is good.

330
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:02,056
HARVEY:
Yeah, and I told him that.

331
00:12:02,139 --> 00:12:03,808
And he doesn't want
to risk putting a target

332
00:12:03,891 --> 00:12:05,768
on his back and then find out
commuting his sentence

333
00:12:05,851 --> 00:12:07,353
really means
cutting it in half.

334
00:12:07,436 --> 00:12:09,647
He's not risking anything.
No one's going to find out.

335
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:11,941
I'm sure that's exactly
what Frank Gallo thought.

336
00:12:12,024 --> 00:12:14,360
So, either put it in writing
or we don't have a deal.

337
00:12:16,654 --> 00:12:18,489
He didn't go for it, did he?

338
00:12:18,614 --> 00:12:19,615
What are you talking about?

339
00:12:19,698 --> 00:12:21,409
Mike being at risk
has nothing to do

340
00:12:21,492 --> 00:12:22,576
with putting
anything in writing.

341
00:12:22,660 --> 00:12:23,994
And you told me
he wouldn't go for it.

342
00:12:24,078 --> 00:12:26,580
So, Harvey,
tell me the truth.

343
00:12:28,165 --> 00:12:30,251
All right, he said no.
But, Sean,

344
00:12:30,334 --> 00:12:31,460
I'm telling you
he'll come around.

345
00:12:31,544 --> 00:12:32,711
He just needs
a couple of days.

346
00:12:32,795 --> 00:12:35,172
Do you know
how many strings I pulled
to put this thing in motion?

347
00:12:35,256 --> 00:12:37,466
What I know is you wouldn't
have pulled anything

348
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:39,093
if this case
wasn't huge for you.

349
00:12:39,176 --> 00:12:41,053
So, instead of yelling at me
for saying that it's going

350
00:12:41,137 --> 00:12:43,639
to take a couple days,
why don't you just give me
a couple of days?

351
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:45,975
Okay, Harvey,
the deal's still
on the table.

352
00:12:46,225 --> 00:12:47,601
But if I find a way
to move forward

353
00:12:47,685 --> 00:12:49,145
without his help,
there is no deal,

354
00:12:49,228 --> 00:12:50,688
and he does
the whole two years.

355
00:13:05,661 --> 00:13:06,704
Jessica.

356
00:13:06,787 --> 00:13:07,788
Harvey.

357
00:13:07,872 --> 00:13:09,081
What's going on with Mike?

358
00:13:09,165 --> 00:13:10,875
I gave him Cahill's offer.

359
00:13:11,542 --> 00:13:13,294
And he's thinking about it?
I'm working on it.

360
00:13:13,377 --> 00:13:15,129
Well, in the meantime,
while you were out,

361
00:13:15,212 --> 00:13:16,922
I got a call
from Nathan Byrnes.

362
00:13:17,006 --> 00:13:18,632
He thinks someone's trying
to take over his company.

363
00:13:18,716 --> 00:13:19,800
Why the hell
would he think that?

364
00:13:19,884 --> 00:13:21,886
Because word on the street
is someone's selling off

365
00:13:21,969 --> 00:13:23,137
a block of his stock.

366
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,221
That doesn't make sense.

367
00:13:24,305 --> 00:13:26,098
We bought Sutter's
shares from him.

368
00:13:27,391 --> 00:13:29,185
Those goddamn traders.
No way.

369
00:13:29,268 --> 00:13:30,603
They wouldn't do that
without telling me.

370
00:13:30,686 --> 00:13:32,396
They bought it in good faith.
Well, they're dumping it

371
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,647
in bad faith.

372
00:13:35,399 --> 00:13:36,901
I'll take care of it.
No.

373
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:38,569
You have your hands
full with Mike.

374
00:13:39,403 --> 00:13:40,571
I can handle this.

375
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:42,531
Jessica, it was my idea
to involve them.

376
00:13:42,615 --> 00:13:43,991
I should be the one
to take care of it.

377
00:13:44,074 --> 00:13:45,743
I don't care
whose idea it was, Harvey.

378
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:47,286
You take care of Mike.

379
00:13:56,295 --> 00:13:57,505
(PHONE RINGING)

380
00:14:01,008 --> 00:14:02,009
Hello?

381
00:14:02,092 --> 00:14:04,720
AUTOMATED VOICE:
<i>You have a call from
Danbury Federal Prison.</i>

382
00:14:04,803 --> 00:14:06,013
<i>Do you accept the charges?</i>

383
00:14:06,096 --> 00:14:07,306
Yes, of course.

384
00:14:08,516 --> 00:14:10,142
<i>Mike, is everything okay?</i>

385
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:12,269
Yeah. Yeah, everything's fine.

386
00:14:12,436 --> 00:14:14,021
I was just thinking
about you.

387
00:14:14,271 --> 00:14:15,856
I was thinking
about you, too.

388
00:14:15,940 --> 00:14:17,024
You were?
Yes.

389
00:14:17,107 --> 00:14:20,027
In fact, I was just
in the middle of a heated

390
00:14:20,110 --> 00:14:21,320
discussion with you about

391
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:23,739
the best way to handle
a death row appeal.

392
00:14:23,822 --> 00:14:24,865
I don't understand.

393
00:14:24,949 --> 00:14:26,867
<i>I took on
an Innocence Project case</i>

394
00:14:26,951 --> 00:14:29,036
just to have something
to take my mind off
of our troubles.

395
00:14:29,119 --> 00:14:30,120
But I...

396
00:14:31,205 --> 00:14:33,332
I didn't want
to take my mind off of you.

397
00:14:33,415 --> 00:14:36,835
<i>So, I figured I would
just imagine we were working
on it together.</i>

398
00:14:37,127 --> 00:14:38,420
I don't know what to say.

399
00:14:39,129 --> 00:14:40,589
<i>Say you're in.</i>

400
00:14:41,924 --> 00:14:44,134
I mean, that depends
on what strategy
we landed on.

401
00:14:44,218 --> 00:14:45,302
<i>Mike, seriously.</i>

402
00:14:45,469 --> 00:14:47,012
Is there something wrong?
MIKE: <i>No.</i>

403
00:14:47,096 --> 00:14:48,556
<i>I just wanted to make sure
you were doing okay.</i>

404
00:14:49,974 --> 00:14:51,559
And that...

405
00:14:51,642 --> 00:14:53,143
That we were still good.

406
00:14:53,477 --> 00:14:55,145
<i>Now that I have
something to take my mind</i>

407
00:14:55,229 --> 00:14:56,355
<i>off our situation</i>

408
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:58,857
and connect me
to you at the same time...

409
00:14:59,858 --> 00:15:00,859
Yeah.

410
00:15:01,485 --> 00:15:02,736
We're better than good.

411
00:15:07,449 --> 00:15:10,077
Then can you do me a favor
and transfer me to Donna?

412
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,829
Of course.
Can I ask why?

413
00:15:12,454 --> 00:15:14,415
I only get one phone call
and I'm pretty sure

414
00:15:14,498 --> 00:15:16,125
she had something
to do with the idea

415
00:15:16,208 --> 00:15:19,378
of you imagining us
working together.

416
00:15:19,461 --> 00:15:21,422
So, I just want to thank her.
<i>Okay.</i>

417
00:15:22,047 --> 00:15:24,174
I love you.
MIKE: <i>I love you, too.</i>

418
00:15:26,677 --> 00:15:27,928
(RINGING)

419
00:15:28,637 --> 00:15:29,763
Hello?

420
00:15:29,847 --> 00:15:31,348
RACHEL: <i>Donna,
I have Mike on the phone.</i>

421
00:15:31,432 --> 00:15:32,558
Put him through.

422
00:15:33,684 --> 00:15:34,768
Hello?
MIKE: <i>Donna.</i>

423
00:15:34,852 --> 00:15:36,270
If Harvey's there,
do me a favor.

424
00:15:36,353 --> 00:15:37,896
Keep your voice down,
and don't tell him it's me.

425
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:39,273
Mike, what's going on?

426
00:15:39,356 --> 00:15:40,941
I'm not taking
the deal, Donna.

427
00:15:41,025 --> 00:15:42,192
Are you crazy?

428
00:15:42,276 --> 00:15:43,360
<i>It's not that simple.</i>

429
00:15:43,444 --> 00:15:44,820
What's not simple about it?

430
00:15:44,903 --> 00:15:46,614
Harvey said that if you...
<i>I don't care what Harvey said.</i>

431
00:15:46,697 --> 00:15:49,116
Because what he didn't say
is that if I do what he wants

432
00:15:49,199 --> 00:15:50,534
and someone finds out,
then I may never get back

433
00:15:50,618 --> 00:15:52,453
to Rachel at all.
<i>Harvey would never</i>

434
00:15:52,536 --> 00:15:53,954
<i>let them find out.</i>
Donna, look, I called you

435
00:15:54,038 --> 00:15:55,623
so that I didn't have to have
this argument with him.

436
00:15:55,706 --> 00:15:57,583
Now, I don't have much time.

437
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:59,335
Are you going
to do this for me or not?

438
00:16:00,294 --> 00:16:01,962
I'll tell him.
<i>Then I also need you</i>

439
00:16:02,046 --> 00:16:03,297
<i>to tell him
something else for me.</i>

440
00:16:03,756 --> 00:16:05,716
If he comes here
to try to change my mind,

441
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:07,843
I'm not going to see him.

442
00:16:09,345 --> 00:16:10,346
(MIKE HANGS UP)

443
00:16:14,558 --> 00:16:15,976
You mind telling me
who the hell said

444
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:18,646
you can dump Nathan Byrnes'
stock without talking to us?

445
00:16:18,729 --> 00:16:19,813
I don't know what you're
talking about.

446
00:16:19,897 --> 00:16:20,981
Who's Nathan Byrnes?

447
00:16:21,065 --> 00:16:22,399
CEO of Exodyne.

448
00:16:22,483 --> 00:16:23,817
Oh, that Nathan Byrnes.

449
00:16:23,901 --> 00:16:26,987
In that case,
I said I could sell
that stock because I own it.

450
00:16:27,071 --> 00:16:30,741
Just like I own this one
and this one and this one.

451
00:16:30,991 --> 00:16:32,534
Hey, look at that.
My Neubacher Capital

452
00:16:32,618 --> 00:16:34,119
position's going
through the roof.

453
00:16:34,203 --> 00:16:35,996
That's not the deal you made
with Harvey, and you know it.

454
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:38,165
Welcome to the big bad
world of Wall Street.

455
00:16:38,248 --> 00:16:40,501
Now, do you want something
or can I get back to work?

456
00:16:40,584 --> 00:16:42,336
Oh, I want something.
You're going to unwind

457
00:16:42,419 --> 00:16:43,837
that sale and buy
those shares back.

458
00:16:43,921 --> 00:16:45,714
At a premium?
Not going to happen.

459
00:16:45,839 --> 00:16:47,800
I'm your landlord.
And the fact you had
to lease

460
00:16:47,883 --> 00:16:49,426
to me means you don't have
much of an operation.

461
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:51,136
You listen to me,
you little piss-ant.

462
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:52,346
You don't know
who you're messing with.

463
00:16:52,429 --> 00:16:53,806
Then why don't I find out?

464
00:16:53,889 --> 00:16:55,307
Over dinner.

465
00:16:55,391 --> 00:16:56,892
You've got to be
kidding me.

466
00:16:56,975 --> 00:16:59,395
You want me to have dinner
with you in exchange

467
00:16:59,478 --> 00:17:01,814
for backing off that trade?
I think of it as you get

468
00:17:01,897 --> 00:17:03,691
to have dinner with me
and I choose to back off

469
00:17:03,774 --> 00:17:05,484
that trade
because I am a stand-up guy.

470
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:07,945
Well, let me let you in
on a little something,
there, Stu.

471
00:17:08,112 --> 00:17:10,989
I don't share dinner staring
down the barrel of a shotgun.

472
00:17:11,198 --> 00:17:12,741
So, why don't you
unwind that trade

473
00:17:12,825 --> 00:17:14,159
and then ask me out?

474
00:17:14,243 --> 00:17:16,328
And then we'll see if you're
as charming as you like

475
00:17:16,412 --> 00:17:17,538
to think you are.
You know what?

476
00:17:17,621 --> 00:17:19,164
I am charming.
But I'm not an idiot

477
00:17:19,248 --> 00:17:22,000
and I'm not unwinding
my trade without getting
something in return.

478
00:17:36,557 --> 00:17:37,808
Harvey, I need to talk
to you about something

479
00:17:37,891 --> 00:17:38,934
and you're
not going to like it.

480
00:17:38,976 --> 00:17:41,562
About what?
That was Mike
on the phone before.

481
00:17:41,937 --> 00:17:43,063
Why didn't you get me?

482
00:17:43,147 --> 00:17:44,732
He's not taking
the deal, Harvey.

483
00:17:44,815 --> 00:17:46,108
The hell he isn't.

484
00:17:47,025 --> 00:17:48,318
Where are you going?

485
00:17:48,902 --> 00:17:51,572
To that prison.
Harvey, the reason
he called me and not you

486
00:17:51,655 --> 00:17:53,407
is because he knew you
wouldn't take no for answer.

487
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:54,575
And I'm not going to.

488
00:17:54,658 --> 00:17:56,410
Which is why he said
if you show up there,

489
00:17:56,493 --> 00:17:58,120
he's not going
to leave his cell.

490
00:17:58,203 --> 00:17:59,246
Then get me Rachel.

491
00:17:59,329 --> 00:18:01,248
No, no. Harvey,
you cannot tell her.

492
00:18:01,457 --> 00:18:04,084
Like hell I can't.
She's the only one
who can convince him.

493
00:18:04,168 --> 00:18:06,211
If you tell her that
Mike's not taking a deal

494
00:18:06,295 --> 00:18:08,088
that can get him out,
it will tear her apart.

495
00:18:08,172 --> 00:18:10,924
And if I don't tell her,
he's going to be in there
for two more years.

496
00:18:11,008 --> 00:18:12,009
Is that what she wants?

497
00:18:12,050 --> 00:18:13,719
That's between them.
That's why I want to
tell her.

498
00:18:13,802 --> 00:18:15,012
She'll make it between them.

499
00:18:15,095 --> 00:18:16,096
Harvey.

500
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:19,016
God damn it.
He plays <i>Checkers</i>
with this guy

501
00:18:19,099 --> 00:18:20,100
and thinks
he owes him his life.

502
00:18:20,184 --> 00:18:21,685
No, that's not fair
and you know it.

503
00:18:21,769 --> 00:18:23,061
Because Mike's loyalty
is the reason

504
00:18:23,145 --> 00:18:24,188
you're not in prison.

505
00:18:26,190 --> 00:18:28,400
That's what's
killing me, Donna.
Don't you understand?

506
00:18:29,359 --> 00:18:34,114
He's in there instead of me
with a guy I put away.

507
00:18:34,490 --> 00:18:37,159
And I can't just sit here
doing nothing

508
00:18:37,242 --> 00:18:39,286
when he has a chance
to get out.

509
00:18:39,536 --> 00:18:41,371
Which is why you have
to think of something else.

510
00:18:42,206 --> 00:18:43,707
Because if you tell Rachel
about this,

511
00:18:43,791 --> 00:18:45,876
the life that's waiting
for Mike when he gets out,

512
00:18:47,002 --> 00:18:48,212
it isn't going to be there.

513
00:18:57,429 --> 00:18:58,430
Harvey.

514
00:18:58,806 --> 00:19:00,349
I'm surprised
to see you here so soon.

515
00:19:00,432 --> 00:19:01,809
I didn't think you'd
turn him this fast.

516
00:19:01,892 --> 00:19:03,727
I need more time.
I don't think you understand.

517
00:19:03,811 --> 00:19:05,896
I'm being pressured to move
to another investigation.

518
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:07,439
You've got 24 hours
to change his mind

519
00:19:07,523 --> 00:19:08,607
or this thing is done.

520
00:19:08,690 --> 00:19:10,150
Then I need you
to do something for me.

521
00:19:10,234 --> 00:19:11,318
I am doing something for you.

522
00:19:11,401 --> 00:19:12,694
I'm getting Mike
out of prison.

523
00:19:12,778 --> 00:19:14,613
Well, you need
to do something else for me

524
00:19:14,696 --> 00:19:16,323
or that's never
going to happen.

525
00:19:17,241 --> 00:19:18,534
What are you talking about?

526
00:19:19,076 --> 00:19:20,828
I need you to get
into a room with him

527
00:19:20,911 --> 00:19:23,038
because he won't listen
to what I have to say.

528
00:19:23,121 --> 00:19:24,456
What exactly
do you want me to tell him

529
00:19:24,540 --> 00:19:25,541
that you haven't already?

530
00:19:25,624 --> 00:19:27,167
Sean, Mike's a bleeding heart.

531
00:19:27,251 --> 00:19:29,336
You need to make
the case directly to him.

532
00:19:29,419 --> 00:19:32,130
He needs to see
the victims of whatever
the hell this guy did.

533
00:19:32,214 --> 00:19:34,424
That's a swell idea, Harvey.
But if I go into that prison

534
00:19:34,508 --> 00:19:36,718
and someone sees me,
not only are we dead
in the water,

535
00:19:36,802 --> 00:19:38,220
but Mike's life
isn't worth shit.

536
00:19:38,303 --> 00:19:40,681
You think I don't know that?
What the hell do you think
I'm doing here?

537
00:19:40,764 --> 00:19:42,641
What are you talking about?
I have a plan,

538
00:19:42,724 --> 00:19:44,601
but you're
not going to like it.
Why not?

539
00:19:44,685 --> 00:19:46,520
Because I need you
to pull another string

540
00:19:46,603 --> 00:19:48,939
and I need you to do it
before Frank Gallo tries

541
00:19:49,022 --> 00:19:50,357
something else with Mike.

542
00:19:59,157 --> 00:20:00,492
All right, fake lawyer.

543
00:20:00,576 --> 00:20:01,827
Let's see what you got.

544
00:20:03,579 --> 00:20:05,122
You're going to let me look
into it for you?

545
00:20:05,205 --> 00:20:06,790
Look into it, shit.

546
00:20:06,999 --> 00:20:08,750
You're going to get me
out of here like you promised.

547
00:20:08,834 --> 00:20:09,918
I never promised.

548
00:20:10,002 --> 00:20:11,461
I said there was an excellent
chance you could get...

549
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:12,880
Six weeks, brother.

550
00:20:12,963 --> 00:20:14,464
I'll be counting the days.

551
00:20:15,966 --> 00:20:17,759
I'll file the motion
first thing in the morning.

552
00:20:17,885 --> 00:20:18,886
There you go.

553
00:20:18,969 --> 00:20:20,846
That's what
I'm talking about.

554
00:20:21,013 --> 00:20:23,307
And if I find out you're
screwing me on any level,

555
00:20:23,807 --> 00:20:26,476
you better hole up in some
dark corner of this prison

556
00:20:26,727 --> 00:20:28,687
and pray to God
I don't find your ass.

557
00:20:36,653 --> 00:20:38,071
What was that all about?

558
00:20:40,407 --> 00:20:42,743
Looks like he took me up
on my offer after all.

559
00:20:56,006 --> 00:20:58,300
God damn it, Gretchen,
where the hell is she?
Where the hell is who?

560
00:20:58,383 --> 00:21:00,010
That architect
you were supposed to call.

561
00:21:00,093 --> 00:21:02,429
She's not supposed to be here
for another half hour.

562
00:21:02,512 --> 00:21:04,097
And if I want
someone's business,

563
00:21:04,181 --> 00:21:06,058
I show up a half hour
early at the latest.

564
00:21:06,141 --> 00:21:07,851
And what exactly
are you looking
to have me do

565
00:21:07,935 --> 00:21:09,186
about your little conundrum?

566
00:21:09,269 --> 00:21:10,812
I want you to give her
a call and tell her

567
00:21:10,896 --> 00:21:12,648
if she doesn't have
the goddamn common courtesy

568
00:21:12,731 --> 00:21:14,942
to show up early,
then she might as well
not show up at all.

569
00:21:15,025 --> 00:21:16,151
Mr. Litt.
Ah...

570
00:21:16,735 --> 00:21:18,278
Yes.

571
00:21:18,362 --> 00:21:21,365
I'm Tara Messer.
I'm here to discuss
your remodel needs.

572
00:21:21,448 --> 00:21:23,116
My needs?
GRETCHEN: Well, I'm sorry,

573
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,952
Ms. Was Going To Be
Our Architect,

574
00:21:25,035 --> 00:21:26,036
we no longer need
your services.

575
00:21:26,119 --> 00:21:27,245
Gretchen, calm down.

576
00:21:27,329 --> 00:21:29,122
You are overreacting
like a crazy woman.

577
00:21:29,206 --> 00:21:30,332
You're hired.

578
00:21:30,415 --> 00:21:31,792
I am?
Oh, yeah.

579
00:21:31,875 --> 00:21:34,044
You're right for the job.
I can feel it.

580
00:21:34,127 --> 00:21:35,629
Oh, you can feel something,
all right.

581
00:21:35,712 --> 00:21:36,922
Then why don't we start

582
00:21:37,005 --> 00:21:38,757
with what you're
looking for in the space?

583
00:21:39,925 --> 00:21:41,343
Oh, the space.

584
00:21:41,551 --> 00:21:42,636
Right, the space.

585
00:21:42,719 --> 00:21:45,555
Exactly. What I'm looking for
are clear, yet unobtrusive

586
00:21:45,639 --> 00:21:47,683
boundaries between
our offices and the tenants'.

587
00:21:47,766 --> 00:21:52,062
But it needs to be elegant
and organic or we might
as well not do it at all.

588
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:53,397
I understand.

589
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:57,150
Like the perfect aria
leading seamlessly

590
00:21:57,234 --> 00:21:58,735
to its inevitable cadenza.

591
00:21:58,819 --> 00:22:00,028
You're an opera lover.

592
00:22:00,112 --> 00:22:01,196
Second only to the ballet.

593
00:22:01,279 --> 00:22:02,656
Then I suggest
we start with a marriage.

594
00:22:02,739 --> 00:22:03,949
I mean, a tour.

595
00:22:13,959 --> 00:22:14,960
Excuse me.

596
00:22:15,085 --> 00:22:16,503
Professor Dunbar.
Do you have a moment?

597
00:22:16,586 --> 00:22:18,255
This is the faculty lounge,
Ms. Zane.

598
00:22:18,338 --> 00:22:19,339
You're not supposed
to be in here.

599
00:22:19,423 --> 00:22:20,674
I understand that.
And I'm sorry.

600
00:22:20,757 --> 00:22:21,842
It's just,
this is important

601
00:22:21,925 --> 00:22:23,260
and you weren't
in your office.

602
00:22:23,927 --> 00:22:25,053
What can I do for you?

603
00:22:25,137 --> 00:22:27,347
I met with Leonard Bailey
yesterday.

604
00:22:27,431 --> 00:22:28,724
He's the inmate on death...
I know who he is.

605
00:22:28,807 --> 00:22:30,600
Is there a problem?
Yes, there is.

606
00:22:30,684 --> 00:22:32,185
He's rotting on death row

607
00:22:32,269 --> 00:22:33,895
for a crime
that he didn't commit.

608
00:22:33,979 --> 00:22:36,023
So, you met with him
for 10 minutes

609
00:22:36,106 --> 00:22:37,482
and you're ready
to release him.

610
00:22:37,566 --> 00:22:38,692
No, what I'm saying is...
You're a second-year

611
00:22:38,775 --> 00:22:40,110
law student, Rachel.

612
00:22:40,193 --> 00:22:42,863
I asked you to be a part
of this because you're
one of my brightest students,

613
00:22:42,946 --> 00:22:44,281
but I also asked you
in particular

614
00:22:44,364 --> 00:22:46,867
because I didn't think
you'd be so naive.

615
00:22:46,950 --> 00:22:48,035
Excuse me?

616
00:22:48,118 --> 00:22:50,579
Your job wasn't to talk
to Mr. Bailey once and,

617
00:22:50,662 --> 00:22:52,497
after being moved
by his tale of woe,

618
00:22:52,581 --> 00:22:54,541
tell me to jump him
to the top of the pile.

619
00:22:54,624 --> 00:22:56,960
It was to assess his case
and present evidence.

620
00:22:57,044 --> 00:22:58,420
And that's exactly
what I'm doing here.

621
00:22:58,503 --> 00:23:01,715
I just left two boxes
of textbook
prosecutorial misconduct

622
00:23:01,798 --> 00:23:03,216
with your secretary.

623
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:05,761
You found
all of that since yesterday.

624
00:23:05,844 --> 00:23:07,471
Yes. Because while
I may only

625
00:23:07,554 --> 00:23:09,264
be a second-year law student,
I have been a practicing

626
00:23:09,347 --> 00:23:11,641
paralegal for the past
eight years.

627
00:23:13,018 --> 00:23:15,145
Looks like I have
some reading to do.

628
00:23:16,980 --> 00:23:18,440
I'm sorry
for interrupting your day.

629
00:23:18,523 --> 00:23:20,150
Good afternoon, Ms. Zane.

630
00:23:20,650 --> 00:23:21,777
Good afternoon, Professor.

631
00:23:27,324 --> 00:23:29,868
And then we use
the glass motif
you already have

632
00:23:29,993 --> 00:23:32,996
to partition their space
from yours starting
at that wall over there.

633
00:23:34,164 --> 00:23:36,750
And no one ever knows
they're two separate entities.

634
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:39,127
And if we use
the frosted glass,

635
00:23:39,211 --> 00:23:41,171
you'll never even have
to lay eyes on them.

636
00:23:41,254 --> 00:23:42,923
Well, there's just
one more thing.

637
00:23:43,006 --> 00:23:44,758
You want to know
if I can design another

638
00:23:44,841 --> 00:23:46,134
bullpen area
for your side.

639
00:23:46,218 --> 00:23:47,928
After all, it's the heart
and soul of the space.

640
00:23:48,011 --> 00:23:50,430
You get that?
It's my job to get that.

641
00:23:51,181 --> 00:23:52,182
I don't understand.

642
00:23:52,265 --> 00:23:55,393
To me, architecture isn't
just about design.

643
00:23:55,477 --> 00:23:57,187
It's... It's about
connecting with my clients

644
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:58,522
on an intimate level.

645
00:23:59,106 --> 00:24:00,482
Well, you're very good at it.

646
00:24:01,024 --> 00:24:03,652
You know, it's too bad
you already sublet
to someone else.

647
00:24:03,735 --> 00:24:05,278
We're looking
to expand ourselves.

648
00:24:05,362 --> 00:24:06,780
This space
would have been perfect.

649
00:24:06,863 --> 00:24:08,573
Are you serious?
Yeah.

650
00:24:08,865 --> 00:24:10,492
In fact, it's so perfect,
I would have made you

651
00:24:10,575 --> 00:24:12,452
an offer on the spot.

652
00:24:12,536 --> 00:24:15,872
Anyway, I'll have some plans
drawn up as soon as I can.

653
00:24:26,341 --> 00:24:27,467
We need to get rid
of those traders.

654
00:24:27,551 --> 00:24:28,552
Excuse me?

655
00:24:28,635 --> 00:24:30,637
I don't care
what kind of deal you
and Harvey cut with them.

656
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:32,514
We need to get rid of them
and we need to do it now.

657
00:24:32,597 --> 00:24:33,890
Well, Louis,
I'm not going to do that.

658
00:24:33,974 --> 00:24:35,517
Because whoever
we replace them with,

659
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,519
this conversation
is just going
to happen again.

660
00:24:37,602 --> 00:24:39,604
Because we both know
that you're out of your mind.

661
00:24:39,688 --> 00:24:40,689
It's not going
to happen again.

662
00:24:40,772 --> 00:24:41,982
Because
in this particular case,

663
00:24:42,065 --> 00:24:43,191
I am not out of my mind.

664
00:24:43,275 --> 00:24:44,276
Why do you
want me to do this?

665
00:24:44,359 --> 00:24:45,902
Because I'm in love
with an architect.

666
00:24:46,236 --> 00:24:47,320
Let me get this straight.

667
00:24:47,404 --> 00:24:49,156
You want me to further
antagonize people

668
00:24:49,239 --> 00:24:50,615
that I'm already
fighting with
because you don't have

669
00:24:50,699 --> 00:24:51,867
the balls to ask
a woman out on a date.

670
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:52,951
That's one way
of looking at it.

671
00:24:53,034 --> 00:24:54,661
No, there's another way.
The answer is no.

672
00:24:54,744 --> 00:24:55,829
Okay, fine.

673
00:24:55,912 --> 00:24:57,497
I'll just stick
to the original plan

674
00:24:57,581 --> 00:24:58,832
of having her completely
redesign our space.

675
00:24:58,915 --> 00:25:00,208
And I'll just make sure
it takes long enough

676
00:25:00,292 --> 00:25:01,334
for her to fall madly
in love with me.

677
00:25:01,418 --> 00:25:02,878
And it shouldn't take
more than two or three years.

678
00:25:02,961 --> 00:25:04,921
Louis, I want you
to look at me
when I say this.

679
00:25:06,006 --> 00:25:08,842
If you hire this woman
to do anything relating

680
00:25:08,925 --> 00:25:11,178
to this firm's space,
I will personally

681
00:25:11,261 --> 00:25:12,596
throw you off the roof
of this building.

682
00:25:12,679 --> 00:25:13,847
Is that clear?

683
00:25:14,431 --> 00:25:16,266
So, you'll think about it?
Get out.

684
00:25:22,105 --> 00:25:23,106
Yo.

685
00:25:23,231 --> 00:25:24,316
(IN AUSTRIAN ACCENT) Ahnold.

686
00:25:24,691 --> 00:25:27,027
Come on.
Let's see what you got.

687
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:29,154
I didn't know you played.
Played?

688
00:25:29,237 --> 00:25:32,657
Shit. I set
the P.S. 92 single game
scoring record.

689
00:25:33,617 --> 00:25:36,369
P.S. 92 is
an elementary school,
my friend.

690
00:25:36,453 --> 00:25:38,580
Yeah, sixth grade.
I dominated.

691
00:25:39,414 --> 00:25:42,209
KEVIN: I thought you had
to file that motion
for Gallo's parole.

692
00:25:42,292 --> 00:25:43,668
MIKE: I did.
Already?

693
00:25:43,752 --> 00:25:45,378
It was an 18-page
sentencing amendment.

694
00:25:45,462 --> 00:25:46,546
I could do that in my sleep.

695
00:25:46,630 --> 00:25:48,423
I should get you
to do some work for me.

696
00:25:48,506 --> 00:25:50,050
Why? You need some?

697
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:51,968
No, but if I did,
I'd probably get myself

698
00:25:52,052 --> 00:25:54,012
a lawyer who didn't sleep
in a prison.

699
00:25:55,305 --> 00:25:56,514
(CLEARS THROAT)

700
00:25:56,890 --> 00:25:58,308
You all right?
(CLEARS THROAT)

701
00:25:58,892 --> 00:26:00,560
I don't...
I don't know.

702
00:26:00,644 --> 00:26:01,686
What do you mean,
you don't know?

703
00:26:01,770 --> 00:26:03,188
(COUGHS)
What is it, your stomach?

704
00:26:03,813 --> 00:26:04,898
Oh, my God.
Something's not right.

705
00:26:04,981 --> 00:26:06,733
Take a deep breath.
Put your head down.

706
00:26:06,816 --> 00:26:09,069
Oh, God. I can't.
That's not going
to do anything.

707
00:26:09,152 --> 00:26:10,195
I think...

708
00:26:10,278 --> 00:26:12,072
Oh, my God, I think
somebody did something to me.

709
00:26:12,155 --> 00:26:13,740
Hey, can I get
some help over here?

710
00:26:13,823 --> 00:26:15,867
Guard! Mike, talk to me.

711
00:26:15,951 --> 00:26:17,869
(BREATHES HEAVILY)
It's Gallo.

712
00:26:17,994 --> 00:26:19,913
Gallo must have put
something in my...

713
00:26:19,996 --> 00:26:21,957
Somebody do something!
Guard!

714
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:23,416
Call Harvey.

715
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:24,751
Guard!

716
00:26:24,834 --> 00:26:25,877
Mike.

717
00:26:26,544 --> 00:26:27,629
Mike!

718
00:26:38,848 --> 00:26:39,933
Where is he?

719
00:26:40,016 --> 00:26:41,935
If I knew who
you were talking about,
maybe I could...

720
00:26:42,018 --> 00:26:43,478
Mike Ross.
I need to see him right now.

721
00:26:43,561 --> 00:26:45,272
And who are you?
Harvey Specter.

722
00:26:45,355 --> 00:26:46,564
I'm his attorney.

723
00:26:49,901 --> 00:26:51,528
Mr. Ross
is in the infirmary,

724
00:26:51,611 --> 00:26:53,029
but you can't
see him in there.

725
00:26:53,196 --> 00:26:54,406
Then get me the warden.

726
00:26:57,909 --> 00:27:00,287
I don't appreciate
being pushed around,
Mr. Specter.

727
00:27:00,370 --> 00:27:02,247
I don't care.
I want everyone

728
00:27:02,330 --> 00:27:03,540
to know what
happened here today.

729
00:27:03,623 --> 00:27:04,624
They saw what happened.

730
00:27:04,708 --> 00:27:07,085
Yeah, there's a difference
between seeing and knowing.

731
00:27:09,004 --> 00:27:10,797
Are you Kevin Miller?
Who are you?

732
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,841
Harvey Specter.
I'm Mike Ross' lawyer.

733
00:27:12,924 --> 00:27:15,218
Look, I already told
the warden I didn't see
anyone touch his food.

734
00:27:15,302 --> 00:27:17,012
Did you see Frank Gallo
with him?

735
00:27:18,513 --> 00:27:19,639
Did you or didn't you?

736
00:27:19,723 --> 00:27:20,849
Are you trying
to get me killed, man?

737
00:27:20,932 --> 00:27:22,225
Did he touch
his food or not?

738
00:27:23,101 --> 00:27:25,687
Yeah, he did,
last night at dinner.

739
00:27:25,770 --> 00:27:27,647
But Mike offered
to get Gallo parole

740
00:27:27,731 --> 00:27:29,357
and Gallo took him up on it,
so why would he poison him?

741
00:27:29,441 --> 00:27:31,818
Because he didn't really
take Mike up on that offer,

742
00:27:31,901 --> 00:27:33,695
he just did it
to get close to him.

743
00:27:33,778 --> 00:27:36,990
Or he did it to give Mike
a taste of what happens
if he doesn't come through.

744
00:27:37,073 --> 00:27:39,701
Either way,
you stay the hell away
from that son of a bitch.

745
00:27:39,784 --> 00:27:41,828
All right, that's enough.
Let's go.

746
00:27:43,913 --> 00:27:45,123
GALLO: Hey, Counselor.

747
00:27:45,206 --> 00:27:47,667
I heard your boy had
a little tummy ache
out in the yard.

748
00:27:47,751 --> 00:27:49,753
You piece of shit.
You goddamn poisoned him.

749
00:27:49,836 --> 00:27:52,005
Guards, get him out of here.
I didn't do shit.

750
00:27:52,088 --> 00:27:54,174
Why don't you come over here
and say that to my face?

751
00:27:54,257 --> 00:27:55,800
You think I won't?
God damn it.

752
00:27:55,884 --> 00:27:57,677
I said get him back
to his cell!

753
00:27:57,761 --> 00:27:59,262
Hey. This wasn't
part of the deal.

754
00:27:59,346 --> 00:28:02,265
We talked about
you seeing his roommate,
not rushing Frank Gallo.

755
00:28:02,349 --> 00:28:05,268
Yeah, well, my guy's lying
unconscious in the infirmary.

756
00:28:05,352 --> 00:28:06,644
So, sue me.

757
00:28:13,234 --> 00:28:14,861
How did you know Gallo
would take the bait?

758
00:28:14,944 --> 00:28:16,112
Because he's an animal.

759
00:28:16,196 --> 00:28:17,489
And animals always
take the bait.

760
00:28:17,572 --> 00:28:19,908
Well, I'll give you credit
for knowing how
it would go down.

761
00:28:20,450 --> 00:28:22,035
I don't need credit.

762
00:28:22,118 --> 00:28:23,536
I need to know
where Mike Ross is.

763
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:25,372
Where I was instructed
to put him.

764
00:28:25,455 --> 00:28:27,707
Let me tell you something,
Mr. Specter.
I don't know you.

765
00:28:27,791 --> 00:28:29,125
So, in case you're thinking
of trying anything,

766
00:28:29,209 --> 00:28:30,710
that kid has
a monitor on his leg.

767
00:28:30,794 --> 00:28:32,629
And if it goes dark
for even one second,

768
00:28:32,712 --> 00:28:35,215
I'm going to make sure
that you end up
in a cell here with him.

769
00:28:35,298 --> 00:28:38,760
It's not going to go dark
and he'll be back here
when I said he would.

770
00:28:38,843 --> 00:28:43,264
Then, after that,
I'm going to make sure
he gets out of here. For good.

771
00:29:10,834 --> 00:29:12,669
HARVEY:
How are you feeling?

772
00:29:18,425 --> 00:29:19,592
What's going on?

773
00:29:20,844 --> 00:29:21,845
Where am I?

774
00:29:22,262 --> 00:29:24,681
You're in the back of my car.
You were drugged.

775
00:29:26,516 --> 00:29:28,518
By Gallo.
By me.

776
00:29:30,770 --> 00:29:32,647
What?
Cahill got the warden

777
00:29:32,730 --> 00:29:34,774
and the prison doctor
to put something
in your food.

778
00:29:34,858 --> 00:29:36,401
They're the only ones
who know what's going on.

779
00:29:36,484 --> 00:29:37,819
What the hell
are you talking about?

780
00:29:37,986 --> 00:29:40,447
We needed to change your mind
about taking this deal.

781
00:29:40,530 --> 00:29:42,365
And we couldn't do it
as long as you're in there.

782
00:29:42,449 --> 00:29:44,701
Jesus Christ.
So, you drugged me?

783
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,328
We needed a cover for why
you're not in your cell,

784
00:29:47,412 --> 00:29:48,746
and this was
the only way to do it.

785
00:29:48,830 --> 00:29:51,124
Are you insane?
You broke me out of prison?

786
00:29:51,207 --> 00:29:52,542
I didn't break you
out of anywhere.

787
00:29:52,625 --> 00:29:53,793
Cahill sanctioned it.

788
00:29:53,877 --> 00:29:56,045
And if anyone's insane,
it's you.

789
00:29:56,129 --> 00:29:57,797
Because you're the one
turning down a chance

790
00:29:57,881 --> 00:29:59,132
to get out of that place.

791
00:29:59,215 --> 00:30:01,009
But we don't have time
to talk about that right now.

792
00:30:01,092 --> 00:30:02,135
Cahill's waiting for us.

793
00:30:02,218 --> 00:30:03,720
You got me out
to see Cahill?

794
00:30:03,803 --> 00:30:04,971
I said he's waiting.

795
00:30:05,054 --> 00:30:06,473
I didn't say that's
where I'm taking you.

796
00:30:06,556 --> 00:30:08,558
Well, then, where the hell
are you taking me?

797
00:30:23,740 --> 00:30:25,658
You think me spending
a couple of hours with Rachel

798
00:30:25,742 --> 00:30:27,327
is going
to change my mind?

799
00:30:27,410 --> 00:30:30,079
If it doesn't,
there's something
wrong with you.

800
00:30:31,164 --> 00:30:33,041
So, are you going
to yell at me

801
00:30:33,124 --> 00:30:34,876
or are you going to take
the only chance
you're going to get

802
00:30:34,959 --> 00:30:36,211
to be alone
with the woman you love

803
00:30:36,294 --> 00:30:37,670
for the next two years?

804
00:30:38,922 --> 00:30:41,841
Please tell me
that you did not tell her
about Cahill's offer.

805
00:30:41,925 --> 00:30:43,593
HARVEY: Oh, I wanted to.

806
00:30:44,052 --> 00:30:46,763
But you have Donna to thank
for the fact that I didn't.

807
00:30:51,434 --> 00:30:54,062
What am I supposed
to tell Rachel about
why I'm here?

808
00:30:56,147 --> 00:30:58,483
If it were me,
I'd tell her the truth.

809
00:30:58,566 --> 00:31:00,818
Now, since you
don't want to do that...

810
00:31:02,278 --> 00:31:04,405
You're lucky
I came up with something else.

811
00:31:10,078 --> 00:31:12,205
Wait till it hits 30
and then sell it.

812
00:31:14,082 --> 00:31:15,458
Well, look who it is.

813
00:31:15,625 --> 00:31:17,710
You change your mind
about my offer?

814
00:31:17,794 --> 00:31:18,920
I'm not there just yet.

815
00:31:19,003 --> 00:31:20,797
But I did come to apologize.

816
00:31:20,922 --> 00:31:22,715
I didn't mean
to be so combative before.

817
00:31:22,799 --> 00:31:25,260
You're a proud woman.
I understand. Bygones.

818
00:31:25,635 --> 00:31:28,137
You know, your operation here
is kind of impressive.

819
00:31:28,221 --> 00:31:29,639
You mind if I, uh,
look at one?

820
00:31:29,722 --> 00:31:31,224
You can take
a look at anything
of mine you want.

821
00:31:31,307 --> 00:31:32,308
(CHUCKLES)

822
00:31:34,727 --> 00:31:36,563
Huh. Now, what does

823
00:31:36,646 --> 00:31:38,022
that line right there mean?

824
00:31:39,107 --> 00:31:40,942
What the hell? That's my
Neubacher Capital position.

825
00:31:41,025 --> 00:31:42,402
Well, it seems
to be falling
very quickly.

826
00:31:42,485 --> 00:31:43,820
Is that a good thing?

827
00:31:45,113 --> 00:31:46,072
You did this.

828
00:31:46,155 --> 00:31:47,323
I'm not sure what you mean.

829
00:31:47,407 --> 00:31:50,243
All I did this afternoon
was call my friend
at Jacobson Kearney

