00:31:50,326 --> 00:31:52,036
and have them issue
a press release about their

831
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,580
client's merger negotiations.

832
00:31:53,663 --> 00:31:55,331
I mean, how was I supposed
to know that it would make

833
00:31:55,415 --> 00:31:57,917
your Neubacher position
fall through the floor?

834
00:31:58,001 --> 00:31:59,877
You used the information
I gave you yesterday

835
00:31:59,961 --> 00:32:01,504
about my holdings,
that's how.

836
00:32:01,796 --> 00:32:03,506
That's inside information
and I can prove it.

837
00:32:03,590 --> 00:32:05,758
No, it could have been
if your attorney hadn't

838
00:32:05,842 --> 00:32:07,260
filed your position
with the SEC

839
00:32:07,343 --> 00:32:09,304
10 days earlier
than he had to.

840
00:32:09,387 --> 00:32:10,638
I'm not going to forget this.

841
00:32:10,722 --> 00:32:12,765
Good. Because my operation's
been around a hell

842
00:32:12,849 --> 00:32:13,933
of a lot longer than yours.

843
00:32:14,017 --> 00:32:16,603
And we can be friends
or we can be enemies.

844
00:32:17,145 --> 00:32:19,439
But you mess with me again
and I'll not only
kick you out

845
00:32:19,522 --> 00:32:22,150
of these offices,
I'll put you in the ground.

846
00:32:35,663 --> 00:32:36,664
Rachel.

847
00:32:37,123 --> 00:32:39,125
Oh, my God.

848
00:32:45,715 --> 00:32:47,008
How?

849
00:32:47,342 --> 00:32:48,509
Harvey.

850
00:32:50,053 --> 00:32:52,055
Oh. I don't understand.

851
00:32:52,347 --> 00:32:54,098
I know you know
about Frank Gallo.

852
00:32:54,182 --> 00:32:56,309
But what you don't know
is that they put me

853
00:32:56,392 --> 00:32:58,561
in solitary confinement
for 36 hours.

854
00:32:58,645 --> 00:32:59,646
Oh, my God.

855
00:32:59,729 --> 00:33:01,064
It's okay. I was safe.

856
00:33:01,898 --> 00:33:03,650
Then Harvey made them watch
the video, which showed

857
00:33:03,733 --> 00:33:05,360
that I was only
defending myself.

858
00:33:05,443 --> 00:33:07,612
Turns out they were more
than happy to trade six hours

859
00:33:07,695 --> 00:33:10,740
and an ankle bracelet
to avoid a lawsuit.

860
00:33:12,659 --> 00:33:14,702
We only have six hours?

861
00:33:15,370 --> 00:33:18,081
Yeah. And I don't want
to waste any of it.

862
00:33:42,939 --> 00:33:44,023
Mr. Litt. What are you...

863
00:33:44,107 --> 00:33:45,858
Oh, please, call me Louis.

864
00:33:46,484 --> 00:33:47,944
What can
I do for you, Louis?

865
00:33:48,027 --> 00:33:49,278
Tara, I'm afraid
I have some bad news.

866
00:33:49,362 --> 00:33:50,571
We're not going
to be moving forward

867
00:33:50,655 --> 00:33:52,115
with the renovations
after all.

868
00:33:53,324 --> 00:33:54,450
I'm sorry to hear that.

869
00:33:54,534 --> 00:33:56,119
No, it has nothing
to do with you.

870
00:33:56,202 --> 00:33:58,246
And of course I will
pay you out of my own pocket

871
00:33:58,329 --> 00:33:59,539
for any of the work
you've already done.

872
00:33:59,622 --> 00:34:00,790
That won't be necessary.

873
00:34:00,873 --> 00:34:02,250
Please, Tara, I insist.

874
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:05,878
In that case,
I might as well

875
00:34:05,962 --> 00:34:07,588
at least show you
what I had in mind.

876
00:34:10,425 --> 00:34:13,094
As you can see,
these are just
rough drawings.

877
00:34:13,720 --> 00:34:15,096
Not to me.

878
00:34:15,179 --> 00:34:18,725
Here's the frosted glass wall
curving in an elegant "S"

879
00:34:18,808 --> 00:34:20,435
that separates the space.

880
00:34:21,185 --> 00:34:23,813
It's beautiful.
That's not even
the best part.

881
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:27,108
Because I know how important
the new bullpen is to you,

882
00:34:27,191 --> 00:34:29,569
I modeled it after
the Kimmel Center

883
00:34:29,652 --> 00:34:31,904
in Philadelphia,
and I enclosed
the entire space.

884
00:34:31,988 --> 00:34:32,989
In mahogany.

885
00:34:33,656 --> 00:34:34,949
(EXHALES)

886
00:34:35,032 --> 00:34:36,743
It would
have been exquisite.

887
00:34:36,826 --> 00:34:39,620
But some things
weren't meant to be.

888
00:34:40,955 --> 00:34:41,956
Yeah.

889
00:34:43,541 --> 00:34:44,751
How would you feel
about renovating

890
00:34:44,834 --> 00:34:46,043
my summer house
in the Hamptons?

891
00:34:46,127 --> 00:34:47,462
I appreciate
the thought, Louis,

892
00:34:47,545 --> 00:34:48,671
but I don't do
residential work.

893
00:34:48,755 --> 00:34:51,007
It's not residential.
I use it as a home office.

894
00:34:51,090 --> 00:34:52,592
But it would be so small.

895
00:34:52,675 --> 00:34:53,718
Oh, no,
I want the entire house

896
00:34:53,801 --> 00:34:55,303
to be a satellite
division of the firm.

897
00:34:56,471 --> 00:34:57,472
Are you sure?

898
00:34:58,431 --> 00:35:00,349
I've never been as sure
of anything in my entire life.

899
00:35:03,394 --> 00:35:05,772
Then I look forward
to working with you, Louis.

900
00:35:12,695 --> 00:35:14,906
Sean, what can I do for you?
Where the hell are they?

901
00:35:15,031 --> 00:35:16,407
What?
I've been sitting
in my office

902
00:35:16,491 --> 00:35:17,617
for two hours
waiting for them.

903
00:35:17,700 --> 00:35:19,535
Where the hell are they?
I don't know.

904
00:35:19,619 --> 00:35:20,661
Maybe they're
caught in traffic.

905
00:35:20,745 --> 00:35:21,913
Listen to me.
I can contact the prison

906
00:35:21,996 --> 00:35:23,456
and find out exactly
where they are.

907
00:35:23,539 --> 00:35:25,082
But I do that,
it starts a tornado

908
00:35:25,166 --> 00:35:26,751
of shit with your boss
in the eye of the storm.

909
00:35:26,834 --> 00:35:27,960
So, you're going
to tell me right now

910
00:35:28,044 --> 00:35:29,253
what the hell they're up to.

911
00:35:30,296 --> 00:35:32,256
He's waiting for Mike
outside of his apartment.

912
00:35:32,340 --> 00:35:33,800
Waiting for him to do what?
He's with Rachel.

913
00:35:33,883 --> 00:35:36,219
You've got to be kidding me.
I didn't pull in every favor
I have

914
00:35:36,302 --> 00:35:38,012
so Mike Ross
could have some
conjugal visit.

915
00:35:38,095 --> 00:35:40,056
No, you pulled in every favor
you had so that Harvey

916
00:35:40,139 --> 00:35:41,933
could convince Mike
to do what you wanted.

917
00:35:42,016 --> 00:35:43,601
And this is going
to make that happen.

918
00:35:43,684 --> 00:35:44,811
By getting him laid?

919
00:35:44,894 --> 00:35:46,229
By reminding him
of what he's missing out on

920
00:35:46,312 --> 00:35:47,438
if he doesn't
take your deal.

921
00:35:47,522 --> 00:35:48,856
That wasn't the plan.

922
00:35:50,233 --> 00:35:51,943
Where are you going?
I'm going to go down there

923
00:35:52,026 --> 00:35:53,194
and do what we said
we were going to do.

924
00:35:53,277 --> 00:35:54,779
I'm going to show Mike
the innocent people

925
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:55,988
that lost everything
because of that bastard.

926
00:35:56,072 --> 00:35:57,156
Sean, please.

927
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:59,283
If you do that,
Rachel will find out
about everything

928
00:35:59,367 --> 00:36:00,409
and that can't happen.

929
00:36:00,493 --> 00:36:01,494
Why not?

930
00:36:01,577 --> 00:36:02,995
Because Mike chose prison
over her once.

931
00:36:03,079 --> 00:36:04,664
And if he does it again,
she'll never forgive him.

932
00:36:04,747 --> 00:36:06,457
Mike's problem, not mine.

933
00:36:06,541 --> 00:36:08,584
No, that's Harvey's problem.

934
00:36:08,668 --> 00:36:10,378
He promised Mike
he wouldn't tell her,

935
00:36:10,461 --> 00:36:12,088
and Harvey's
a man of his word.

936
00:36:12,171 --> 00:36:14,298
If he were a man of his word,
he would be here right now.

937
00:36:14,382 --> 00:36:15,967
So, what are you going to do?
I'm going to do what should

938
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:17,301
have been done
in the first place.

939
00:36:17,385 --> 00:36:18,761
I'm going to tell
Mike's fiancÃ©e

940
00:36:18,845 --> 00:36:20,012
that he has
a chance to get out

941
00:36:20,096 --> 00:36:21,472
but he doesn't want
to take it.

942
00:36:23,432 --> 00:36:25,601
You want to tell me
what that was all about?

943
00:36:28,271 --> 00:36:30,273
Harvey and Cahill got Mike
out of prison to convince him

944
00:36:30,356 --> 00:36:31,482
to take the deal.

945
00:36:32,108 --> 00:36:34,861
And Harvey brought Mike
to Rachel instead of to Sean.

946
00:36:34,944 --> 00:36:37,154
He broke Mike
out of prison.

947
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:40,032
Is he crazy?
It sounded crazy
to me at first, too.

948
00:36:40,116 --> 00:36:41,909
But Harvey's living
with the guilt
of putting Mike

949
00:36:41,993 --> 00:36:43,703
in there and Cahill
was willing to do it.

950
00:36:43,786 --> 00:36:44,829
So, can you blame him?

951
00:36:45,705 --> 00:36:47,623
No, I can't.

952
00:36:49,917 --> 00:36:51,878
But I want to know how
this whole thing shakes out.

953
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:53,671
And I want to know tonight.

954
00:37:08,394 --> 00:37:09,645
(GASPS)
Shh.

955
00:37:09,812 --> 00:37:11,397
What time is it?
We still have time.

956
00:37:12,899 --> 00:37:14,025
Oh, my God.

957
00:37:15,067 --> 00:37:16,527
Oh, I fell asleep.

958
00:37:17,862 --> 00:37:18,863
You did.

959
00:37:19,322 --> 00:37:21,157
Why didn't you wake me?

960
00:37:21,824 --> 00:37:23,409
Because you looked
so peaceful.

961
00:37:23,492 --> 00:37:24,577
Rachel, come on.

962
00:37:24,660 --> 00:37:25,786
I don't want us
to waste any...

963
00:37:25,870 --> 00:37:27,079
We're not wasting anything.

964
00:37:27,163 --> 00:37:29,332
Mike, I don't know
how well you sleep in there.

965
00:37:30,166 --> 00:37:32,501
So, to be able
to give you this...

966
00:37:38,925 --> 00:37:39,926
Thank you.

967
00:37:42,219 --> 00:37:44,096
Can I cook you something?

968
00:37:45,097 --> 00:37:46,682
I'll make you
anything you want.

969
00:37:46,766 --> 00:37:49,352
No, I just
want us to lie here
and stare at each other

970
00:37:51,270 --> 00:37:53,230
and not say anything.

971
00:37:56,901 --> 00:37:57,902
Oh, God.

972
00:37:59,528 --> 00:38:01,614
You're so beautiful.

973
00:38:04,617 --> 00:38:06,827
I thought
